{
  "name": "upper-mines",
  "description": "## Irondeep Hold — Upper Mines\n\nThe upper levels of the dwarven mine, now overrun by undead. Ancient dwarven architecture blends with mining equipment and collapsed tunnels.\n\n### Areas\n- **Guard Room** (cells 3,2-7,6): Where mine guards once rotated shifts. Contains weapon racks and supply crates.\n- **Mine Cart Storage** (cells 17,2-21,6): Where mine carts are stored. A spectral mine cart can be triggered to careen down the tracks.\n- **Collapsed Tunnel** (cells 3,10-7,14): A section where the mine collapsed. Trapped miners are behind the rubble.\n- **Armory** (cells 17,10-21,14): The dwarven armory. Ancient weapons line the walls — characters can grab them as bonus actions.\n- **Prison Cells** (cells 3,18-7,22): Where captured townsfolk are held. Kelda is kept here.\n- **Supply Cache** (cells 17,18-21,22): Mining supplies and adventuring gear left by the party.",
